We start by extracting and computing the following figures from the provided statements:

1. Return on Equity (ROE)
 • The Net Profit from the income statement is 112375.10.
 • The owner's equity at the beginning is 16000000.00 and at the end is 16112375.10.
 • We use the average owner’s equity to calculate ROE:
  Average Owner's Equity = (Beginning + Ending) / 2  
    = (16000000.00 + 16112375.10) / 2  
    ≈ 16056187.55  
 • ROE = (Net Profit) / (Average Owner's Equity)  
  = 112375.10 / 16056187.55  
  ≈ 0.0070 or 0.70%

2. Debt to Asset Ratio
 • The liabilities are represented by “Total Current Liabilities” which is 7605149.91.
 • The “Total Assets” is 23717525.01.
 • Debt to Asset Ratio = Liabilities / Assets  
  = 7605149.91 / 23717525.01  
  ≈ 0.3207, and rounded to 0.32

3. Gross Profit Margin
 • The Gross Profit is 279378.77 and the Total Revenue is 775598.77 (from the income statement).
 • Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit) / (Total Revenue)  
  = 279378.77 / 775598.77  
  ≈ 0.3602 or 36.02%

Thus, our final solutions are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "0.70%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.32",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "36.02%"
  }
}
